"02_nil_boolean.mst — UndefinedObject/Boolean/True/False (sprint_s06_detail.md
 #02). True/False's ifTrue:/ifFalse:/and:/or: are the REAL-SEND fallbacks
 for S5's inlined selectors (Pitfalls P6) — semantics must match the
 inlined patterns exactly, incl. ifTrue: answering nil on the untaken leg."

"I am the class of nil, my one instance. nil is the initial value of
 every variable and instance variable, and the conventional answer for
 no result. I answer true to isNil and false to notNil (all other
 objects answer the reverse), I print as nil, and copying me answers
 me."

Object subclass: UndefinedObject [
    isNil [
        ^true
    ]
    notNil [
        ^false
    ]
]

"I am the abstract superclass of True and False, the two truth values.
 My subclasses carry the real protocol: not, & and | (eager — the
 argument is already evaluated), and: and or: (short-circuit — the
 argument is a block run only when needed), the ifTrue:/ifFalse:
 conditionals, and xor:/eqv:. The compiler inlines the common
 conditional forms; my subclasses keep real methods with identical
 semantics for when a Boolean is reached through a dynamic send."

Object subclass: Boolean [
]

"I am the true case of Boolean; the value true is my one instance. My
 methods answer each conditional's true leg directly: ifTrue: runs its
 block, ifFalse: answers nil, and: evaluates its block, or: answers
 true without looking at its argument."

Boolean subclass: True [
    not [
        ^false
    ]
    and: aBlock [
        ^aBlock value
    ]
    or: aBlock [
        ^true
    ]
    ifTrue: aBlock [
        ^aBlock value
    ]
    ifFalse: aBlock [
        ^nil
    ]
    ifTrue: aBlock ifFalse: cBlock [
        ^aBlock value
    ]
    ifFalse: aBlock ifTrue: cBlock [
        ^cBlock value
    ]
    & aBoolean [
        ^aBoolean
    ]
    | aBoolean [
        ^true
    ]
]

"I am the false case of Boolean; the value false is my one instance.
 My methods mirror True with the legs swapped: ifTrue: answers nil,
 ifFalse: runs its block, and: answers false without evaluating its
 argument, or: evaluates its block."

Boolean subclass: False [
    not [
        ^true
    ]
    and: aBlock [
        ^false
    ]
    or: aBlock [
        ^aBlock value
    ]
    ifTrue: aBlock [
        ^nil
    ]
    ifFalse: aBlock [
        ^aBlock value
    ]
    ifTrue: aBlock ifFalse: cBlock [
        ^cBlock value
    ]
    ifFalse: aBlock ifTrue: cBlock [
        ^aBlock value
    ]
    & aBoolean [
        ^false
    ]
    | aBoolean [
        ^aBoolean
    ]
]

nil subclass: Object [
    = anObject [
        ^self == anObject
    ]
    ~= anObject [
        ^(self = anObject) not
    ]
    ~~ anObject [
        ^(self == anObject) not
    ]
    isNil [
        ^false
    ]
    notNil [
        ^true
    ]
    isString [
        ^false
    ]
    isSymbol [
        ^false
    ]
    isInteger [
        ^false
    ]
    isDouble [
        ^false
    ]
    "Defined HERE, beside its sibling predicates, rather than in
     23_fraction.mst where Fraction itself lives: SmallInteger's arithmetic
     fallbacks (06) test `aNumber isFraction`, and they run long before
     file 23 loads (e.g. smallInt + largeInt during 07-22)."
    isFraction [
        ^false
    ]
    isCharacter [
        ^false
    ]
    isClass [
        ^false
    ]
]
